The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 November is 6,856 (793.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 November, there were 871 new confirmed cases (100.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 October, there were 809 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 8% ( 62 extra cases).
